(250,3,"2019-06-12 00:21:51","2019-06-12 00:21:51","<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Recently, we had an agent who wanted to remain anonymous\nreach out to us regarding how he was able to put into practice what we preach.\nThe agent wanted to remain anonymous so we will call her Sheila. Sheila has\nbeen an agent for 8 years operating in secondary markets outside montreal where\nolder sellers are retiring and younger buyers often 15 years her junior are\nlooking for properties. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“I was known in the area as I had a long standing\nrelationship with a lot of the property owners around who had owned chalets for\nyears. As they we’re retiring they turned to me in hopes of getting their\nproperty sold. My issue was my pool of buyers and sellers we’re in the same age\ngroup and although I had great inventory, I wasn’t able to convert much into\nsales”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sheila relied on her in person sales techniques and her\nnetwork of people she knew. But how do you target young couples and attract\nthem to properties that would be a great fit for them? Often times, people are\nlooking at selling their chalets and retiring to warmer climates down south\nwhile younger families want to experience the same memories they had growing up\nby the lake. How do you bring the two very different clients together?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Enter online marketing 101!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“I began by trying a 250$ facebook and Instagram campaign as\nI always saw my daughters and their friends on their phones. I figured the only\nway to reach them was through their smart phones somehow and facebook made it\nreally easy for me to market. The results we’re almost instantaneous and,\nwithin hours of launching my campaign over 1500 people had seen a beautiful\nchalet I had listed with water front access. It was so easy to setup and all I